WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:04,950
When data output rises but outcomes stay flat, decision rhythm is usually the bottleneck.

00:05,000 --> 00:09,950
Volume increases quickly, but analytics quality improves only with explicit review loops.

00:10,000 --> 00:14,950
Pick one owner and one metric, then run one weekly checkpoint in the workstream.

00:15,000 --> 00:19,950
Run a one-week pilot, capture evidence from real behavior, then adjust immediately.

00:20,000 --> 00:24,950
Teams get better adoption, cleaner decisions in review, and fewer repeat corrections in delivery.

00:25,000 --> 00:29,950
Which weekly checkpoint would improve decision quality first?
